00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:25.000
Have you heard of the 1% rule?

116
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.000
Yes.

117
00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.000
If you improve just 1% every day,

118
00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.000
you'll be 37 times better in a year.

119
00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:35.000
That's because small efforts compound over time,

120
00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:38.000
just like interest in a bank account.

121
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:42.000
Exactly. And that ties into the power of habits.

122
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:45.000
James Clear talks about this in atomic habits.

123
00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:48.000
How habits shape our identity?

124
00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:51.000
Small changes may not seem big at first,

125
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:55.000
but they redefine who you are over time.

126
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Right.

127
00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.000
Like reading just 10 minutes a day,

128
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
practicing English for 5 minutes daily,

129
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:05.000
or even replacing negative thoughts with positive affirmations.

130
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:07.000
And I love real life examples.

131
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:10.000
I know someone who became fluent in English

132
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.000
just by listening to podcasts every day.

133
00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
They didn't start with an intense study plan,

134
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.000
just consistent small steps.

135
00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.000
That's so inspiring.

136
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:22.000
The takeaway here is,

137
00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:26.000
small consistent actions lead to big results over time.

138
00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:29.000
So if you're listening and wondering where to start,

139
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.000
just pick one small habit today.

140
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.000
Exactly.

141
00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:37.000
And you know, Aaron, while taking action is important,

142
00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:41.000
there's something even more fundamental, our mindset.

143
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.000
Because let's be honest,

144
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:45.000
how we think about change makes all the difference.

145
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.000
Absolutely.

146
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:51.000
There's something called the growth mindset versus fixed mindset.

147
00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:55.000
If you have a growth mindset, you believe I can improve.

148
00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:58.000
But if you have a fixed mindset,

149
00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:01.000
you think I'll never be good at this.

150
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.000
That's a huge difference.

151
00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:04.000
And another thing,

152
00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
our brain is wired to focus on what we train it to notice.

153
00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:11.000
Have you heard of the reticular activating system?

154
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.000
Yes.

155
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
It's why when you learn a new word,

156
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:17.000
you suddenly hear it everywhere.

157
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:21.000
Your brain filters information based on what you focus on.

158
00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
So if you keep telling yourself,

159
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:24.000
I can't do this.

160
00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:27.000
Your brain will find evidence to prove it.

161
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.000
But if you say,

162
00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:30.000
I am improving every day,

163
00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:33.000
your brain will focus on that progress instead.

164
00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:37.000
That's why reprogramming your mind is so powerful.

165
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.000
Three great ways to do that are affirmations,

166
00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:43.000
visualization, and gratitude.

167
00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.000
Right.

168
00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:46.000
Positive self-talk like,

169
00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.000
I am getting better every day,

170
00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.000
helps reshape our thoughts.

171
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Visualization, seeing yourself succeed,

172
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:56.000
tricks your brain into believing it's possible.

173
00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.000
And don't forget gratitude practice.

174
00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:00.000
When you focus on what's going well,

175
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
you train your brain to see opportunities instead of obstacles.

176
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.000
That's the power of mindset.

177
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:08.000
It's not magic.

178
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:10.000
It's about training your brain to work for you,

179
00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:12.000
not against you.

180
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:14.000
So true.

181
00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:17.000
Now that we've talked about the power of mindset,

182
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:20.000
there's something else that holds people back,

183
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:23.000
waiting for the right moment to start.

184
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:25.000
Yes.

185
00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:29.000
So many people believe that they need to be completely ready

186
00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:31.000
before they take action.

187
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.000
But here's the truth.

188
00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:35.000
You will never feel fully ready.

189
00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:37.000
Exactly.

190
00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:39.000
Progress comes before confidence.

191
00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:41.000
When I was learning English,

192
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:43.000
I hesitated to start speaking

193
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:45.000
because I felt like I wasn't ready.

194
00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
I kept thinking,

195
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:49.000
what if I make mistakes?

196
00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:52.000
But the more I waited, the harder it became.

197
00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:54.000
That's so relatable.

198
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.000
But when you finally took that first step, what happened?

199
00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:00.000
Well, once I started speaking,

200
00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:05.000
I realized that making mistakes was part of the learning process.

201
00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:10.000
Each conversation, even with errors, built my confidence.

202
00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:13.000
I wasn't perfect, but I was improving.

203
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.000
And that's the key.

204
00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.000
There's a concept I love.

205
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:19.000
Done is better than perfect.

206
00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.000
Too many people delay action

207
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:24.000
because they want everything to be just right.

208
00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:29.000
But in reality, imperfect action is always better than no action.

209
00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:30.000
Right.

210
00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:34.000
If you wait for perfection, you'll never get started.

211
00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:37.000
Whether it's learning English, starting a new habit,

212
00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:39.000
or making a big life change.

213
00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.000
Just begin.

214
00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:44.000
Small steps will lead to big improvements over time.

215
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:47.000
So here's a quick challenge for you, our listeners.

216
00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:49.000
